# Icon Usage Guidelines

## Use FontAwesome for all icons with semantic colors

- ALWAYS use `FontAwesome` from `@expo/vector-icons` for all icon needs
- NEVER use emoji or text-based icons (üìÖ, üéÇ, ‚úÖ, etc.)
- Use semantic color classes for icon colors when possible
- For dynamic colors, extract hex values from CSS custom properties
- Maintain consistency with icon sizes across the app

```typescript
// ‚úÖ Correct - Use FontAwesome with semantic colors
import { FontAwesome } from '@expo/vector-icons';

// For static usage, you can use hex values that match the semantic colors
<FontAwesome name="calendar-o" size={18} color="#6b7280" /> // text-icon color
<FontAwesome name="eye" size={20} color="#6b7280" />       // text-icon color
<FontAwesome name="user" size={24} color="#111827" />      // text-text color

// ‚ùå Incorrect - Avoid emojis or random colors
<Text>üìÖ</Text>
<Text>üë§</Text>
<FontAwesome name="calendar-o" size={18} color="#random" />
```

## Icon Patterns

- Use consistent sizing: 16px for small, 20px for medium, 24px for large icons
- Use hex values that match the semantic colors defined in [global.css](mdc:global.css):
  - `#6b7280` for icon color (text-icon)
  - `#111827` for primary text color (text-text)
  - `#2d489a` for primary color
  - `#ef4444` for error color
  - `#10b981` for success color
- Prefer outline versions (-o suffix) for better visual consistency
- Wrap icons in proper containers with consistent spacing

```typescript
// ‚úÖ Standard icon component pattern
const IconComponent = () => (
  <View className="w-6 h-6 items-center justify-center">
    <FontAwesome name="icon-name" size={18} color="#6b7280" />
  </View>
);

// ‚úÖ Common icon names to use
- calendar-o (dates)
- user (profile)
- eye / eye-slash (password visibility)
- home (navigation)
- search (search functionality)
- plus (add actions)
- times (close/cancel)
- check (success/complete)
- exclamation-triangle (warnings)
- info-circle (information)
- birthday-cake (birthday/celebration)
- trending-up (growth/positive stats)
```

## Icon Color Guidelines

Use hex values that correspond to semantic colors:

- `#6b7280` for secondary/muted icons (text-icon)
- `#111827` when icons should match text color (text-text)
- `#2d489a` for primary/interactive icons (primary)
- `#ef4444` for error state icons
- `#10b981` for success state icons
- `#f59e0b` for warning state icons
- `#3b82f6` for info state icons

```typescript
// ‚úÖ Icon color examples with semantic hex values
<FontAwesome name="calendar-o" size={18} color="#6b7280" />  // Secondary/muted
<FontAwesome name="check" size={20} color="#10b981" />       // Success
<FontAwesome name="times" size={18} color="#ef4444" />       // Error
<FontAwesome name="user" size={24} color="#2d489a" />        // Primary
```

## Semantic Color Integration

- Icons should use hex values that match the CSS custom properties
- These values automatically work with the theme system
- Always use the defined semantic color hex values
- NEVER use random or arbitrary color values

```typescript
